markLine.data.0.coord.desc:
 Coordinates of the starting point or ending point, whose format depends on the coordinate of the series. It can be x, and y for [rectangular coordinates][0], or radius, and angle for [polar coordinates][1]. **Notice:** For axis with [axis.type][2]'category': 

* If coord value is number, it represents index of [axis.data][3].
* If coord value is string, it represents concrete value in [axis.data][3]. Please notice that in this case xAxis.data must not be written as [number, number, ...], but can only be written [string, string, ...]. Otherwise it is not able to be located by markPoint / markLine.

For example: 

    {
        xAxis: {
            type: 'category',
            data: ['5', '6', '9', '13', '19', '33']
            // As mentioned above, data should not be [5, 6, 9, 13, 19, 33] here.
        },
        series: {
            type: 'line',
            data: [11, 22, 33, 44, 55, 66],
            markPoint: { // markLine is in the same way.
                data: [{
                    coord: [5, 33.4], // The number 5 represents xAxis.data[5], that is, '33'.
                    // coord: ['5', 33.4] // The string '5' represents the '5' in xAxis.data.
                }]
            }
        }
    }




